Flexbox Cheat Sheet
===

Properties for the Parent
---

display: flex;

1. Main-axis

flex-direction: row; # (default) Left to right
flex-direction: row-direction; # Right to left
flex-direction: column; # Top to bottom
flex-direction: column-reverse; # Bottom to Top
flex-wrap: nowrap; # single-line
flex-wrap: wrap; # multi-line

flex-flow: row wrap; # combine flex-direction & flex-wrap

justify-content: flex-start; # (default) align left
justify-content: flex-end; # align right
justify-content: center; # align center
justify-content: space-around; # align with space
justify-content: space-between; # align with space but not external sides

2. Cross-axis

align-items: stretch; # (default) stretch element on cross-axis for single line
align-items: flex-start; # align on the top for single line
align-items: flex-end; # align on the bottom for single line
align-items: center; # align center for single line

align-content: flex-start # top align for multiline

Properties for the Children
---

order: 1 # order

flex-grow: 2 # space for one element
flex-shrink: 2
flex-basis: 50%
flex: flex-grow flex-shrink flex-basis

align-self: flex-end;

